Package: pubmedRecords
Type: Package
Title: Get and format NCBI PubMed records and their associated bibliometrics as tidy data
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2016-08-07
Author: Peter Kamerman <peter.kamerman@gmail.com>
Maintainer: Peter Kamerman <peter.kamerman@gmail.com>
URL: https://github.com/kamermanpr/pubmedRecords
BugReports: https://github.com/kamermanpr/pubmedRecords/issues
Description: This package provides tools to download records from the NCBI PubMed database based on user-specified search criteria, and to add commonly used bibliometrics for the returned records. The output is always in a tidy data format, making it easy to analyse the data using tools from the 'tidyverse'. 
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
Depends: 
	R (>= 3.3.1),
Imports: 
    	countrycode,
        dplyr,
	magrittr,
	purrr,
	rAltmetric,
	rcrossref,
	stringr,
	tibble,
	tidyr,
	xml2
Suggests: 
	rentrez,
	testthat